        "node_id": "chunk:history_of_west_virginia_0",
        "score": 0.007815006668686598,
        "text": "History of West Virginia\nWest Virginia is one of two American states formed during the American Civil War (1861 -- 1865), along with Nevada, and is the only state to form by seceding from a Confederate state. It was originally part of the British Virginia Colony (1607 -- 1776) and the western part of the state of Virginia (1776 -- 1863), whose population became sharply divided over the issue of secession from the Union and in the separation from Virginia, formalized by admittance to the Union as a new state in 1863. West Virginia was one of the Civil War Border states.",
        "metadata": {
